## E2E test structure

```
e2e/
├── playwright.config.ts       # FRONTEND_URL / BACKEND_URL from .env.local
├── .env.local                 # gitignored — your app's URLs and tokens
├── .env.example               # committed template — copy to .env.local
├── global-setup.ts            # optional DB reset (skipped when SKIP_DB_RESET=true)
├── run-playwright.sh          # Docker wrapper for the test runner
├── run-audit.sh               # governed test runner (writes the audit trail)
├── tmux-cockpit.sh            # remote/k8s cockpit builder (placeholder until configured)
├── tmux-cockpit-local.sh      # local dev cockpit builder (placeholder until configured)
├── governance/                # GOVERNANCE.md, run schema, flaky register
├── test-book/                 # Gherkin chapters + TC-IDs
└── tests/
    ├── helpers.ts             # auth mocks / fixtures
    └── smoke.spec.ts          # @smoke — health + SPA load
```

---

## Key rules

| # | Rule |
|---|------|
| 1 | **Run tests through the runner** — use `./run-audit.sh` (governed) or `./run-playwright.sh` (ad-hoc). |
| 2 | **Never run DB migrations against a shared/production DB** — set `SKIP_DB_RESET=true`. |
| 3 | **UI tests mock auth** — auth failures in UI tests mean a broken mock, not a broken auth server. |
| 4 | **Smoke is the gate** — if `@smoke` fails, fix infrastructure before touching app code. |
| 5 | **Backend logs first** — check the backend pane/window before opening source files. |
| 6 | **One fix per turn** — fix one failing test, verify it, then proceed to the next. |
| 7 | **Always use `run-audit.sh`** for tracked runs — it records the audit trail. |

---

## Running tests

```bash
# From the e2e/ directory
./run-audit.sh --scope "@smoke"          # smoke gate
./run-audit.sh                           # full suite
./run-audit.sh --scope "@{chapter-tag}"  # single chapter
```

## Checking backend connectivity

```bash
curl -sk http://localhost:@@BACKEND_PORT@@@@HEALTH_PATH@@   # 200 = backend alive
```
